1
00:00:35,660 --> 00:00:39,496
「嗨，貨鼓郎」
# Hey, Mister Tambourine Man #

2
00:00:39,664 --> 00:00:42,541
「為我演奏一曲」
# Play a song for me #

3
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:46,587
- 「在這鏗鏘的早晨」 - B
- # In the jingle-jangle morning... # - "B."

4
00:00:46,755 --> 00:00:49,965
- 「讓我與你同去」 - A
- # I'll come following... # - "A."

5
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:51,884
玩得開心嗎？親愛的
Man: You having fun, sweetheart?

6
00:00:52,052 --> 00:00:54,053
是的
Girl: Yes.

7
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:56,847
啊
Ahh.

8
00:00:57,015 --> 00:00:59,850
寶貝，我希望你做得比我好
Well, I hope you're doing better than me, baby.

9
00:01:00,018 --> 00:01:02,436
- 你做的是什麼？ - 為媽媽做的項鏈
- What are you making? - A necklace for Mom.

10
00:01:02,604 --> 00:01:04,688
是嗎？讓我看看
Yeah? Let me see.

11
00:01:04,856 --> 00:01:07,066
哇，又一條？
Wow. Another one?

12
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:09,693
- 是呀 - 親愛的？
- Yes. - Woman: Honey?

13
00:01:09,861 --> 00:01:11,528
今天有兩條了？
That's two today.

14
00:01:11,696 --> 00:01:13,405
- 是呀 - 哦
- Yeah. - Yeah.

15
00:01:13,573 --> 00:01:14,990
親愛的？
Honey?

16
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:17,785
- 在 - 幫我開一下門吧？
- Yeah? - Waiting for the help to get that?

17
00:01:17,952 --> 00:01:20,704
我覺得你和我都是幫手
I thought you and I were the help.

18
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:25,793
- 洗手吃飯去，小南瓜 - 好
- Go wash up for dinner, pumpkin. - Okay.

19
00:01:25,960 --> 00:01:28,420
嗯，聞起來很香 可以外賣嗎？
Mmm, smells nice. That takeout?

20
00:01:30,048 --> 00:01:31,965
媽媽，看…
Mommy, look at-

21
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:41,850
不！
No!

22
00:01:42,018 --> 00:01:44,353
不！啊！
No! Ahh!

23
00:01:47,315 --> 00:01:52,027
哦！別，別，別
Oh! No no no!

24
00:01:52,195 --> 00:01:54,655
你沒法跟天斗
You can't fight fate.

25
00:02:06,084 --> 00:02:09,253
我們得離開這鬼地方了 快走吧！
Man: We gotta get the fuck out of here. Come on!

26
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:13,882
哦，不，不
Oh! Oh no!

27
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:19,304
不！
Thug: No!

28
00:02:19,472 --> 00:02:22,182
- 你他媽在幹什麼？ - 不！
- What the fuck are you doing? - No!

29
00:02:22,350 --> 00:02:24,643
媽的停下！ 我們快走！
Fucking stop! Let's go!

30
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:26,812
他媽給我閉嘴！
Just shut the fuck up!

31
00:02:33,194 --> 00:02:35,154
不！
No!

32
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:45,664
棒極了
It's cool.

33
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:47,332
小孩喜歡我
Kids like me.

34
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:50,502
不，希瑟
No! Heather!

35
00:02:53,256 --> 00:02:56,049
不，不！
No no!

36
00:03:13,733 --> 00:03:17,400
《守法公民》

37
00:03:51,814 --> 00:03:54,691
- 尼克 - 佈雷，怎麼了？
- Nick. - Bray, what's happenin'?

38
00:03:54,859 --> 00:03:58,111
威利斯是我一起划艇的朋友 他小孩的案子怎麼樣了？
Willis is a rowing buddy of mine. Where are we on his kid's case?

39
00:03:58,279 --> 00:03:59,696
- 威利斯？ - 是啊
- Willis? - Yeah.

40
00:03:59,864 --> 00:04:01,615
- 哦，我把他踢到少管所去了 - 為什麼那樣做？
- Oh, I kicked it down to juvie. - Why did you do that?

41
00:04:01,783 --> 00:04:03,700
因為這案子很沒勁 當他承認謀殺時
'Cause the case was a dog. The kid was only 15 years old

42
00:04:03,868 --> 00:04:05,494
這個孩子才只有15歲
when he committed the murder.

43
00:04:05,662 --> 00:04:08,497
你捨得影響你那百分之九十五的定罪率記錄麼
You wouldn't want to jeopardize your 95% conviction rate.

44
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,624
- 其實是百分之九十六 - 現在九十六了？
- It's actually 96%. - 96% now?

45
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:13,126
是的，你得好好記記賬本了
Yes. You gotta keep your books better than that.

46
00:04:15,296 --> 00:04:17,673
你知道，如果我沒理解錯的話 我會說你想取代我的職位
You know, if I didn't know any better, I'd say you were gunning for my job.

47
00:04:17,840 --> 00:04:19,299
你確實說的對
You do know better.

48
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:21,802
而你也該知道我的目標要更高
And you know that I'm aiming much higher than that.

49
00:04:22,804 --> 00:04:24,513
他們請求撤回此案
Woman: They filed a motion to dismiss,

50
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:26,515
但艾布拉姆法官堅持不同意
but there's no way that Judge Abrams honors it.

51
00:04:26,683 --> 00:04:27,891
我想我們可以搬出RICO法令 （反犯罪組織侵蝕合法組織法）
I think that we can get him on RICO.

52
00:04:28,059 --> 00:04:30,560
莎拉,這陣子你就只做了這些?
All that time and that's what you come back with, Sarah?

53
00:04:30,728 --> 00:04:33,563
你也許應該重新評估下自己的能力
You might want to reevaluate your research skills.

54
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:35,565
- 還有其它信息麼? - 她說得對
- What else have we got? - Nick: She's right.

55
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:36,858
什麼意思？
Mr. Rice?

56
00:04:37,026 --> 00:04:38,485
RICO是設計處理這類事情的
RICO's designed for this kind of thing.

57
00:04:38,653 --> 00:04:41,071
查一下《有組織犯罪控制法》901章
Check out section 901 of the Organized Crime Control Act.

58
00:04:41,239 --> 00:04:43,448
你就會讓莎拉處理這個案子
And you should let Sarah try this case too.

59
00:04:43,616 --> 00:04:46,618
瑞斯先生，我記得以前 這屋子是我說的算
Mr. Rice, last I checked, I was running this room.

60
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:49,121
她已經做了案件調查的工作 我會監督這個
She's already done the leg-work. I'll oversee it.

61
00:04:49,289 --> 00:04:51,081
我的意思是海倫·凱勒可以試試這個案子 （海倫·凱勒：上世紀美國傑出女性）
I mean, Helen Keller could try this case.

62
00:04:52,542 --> 00:04:55,836
好吧，青年才俊 她搞砸了，就算在你頭上
Okay, Boy Wonder, she fucks up, it's on you.

63
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:03,927
坎特雷爾想見你
Cantrell wants to see you.

64
00:05:04,095 --> 00:05:05,387
好的，我馬上就去
All right, I'll be right there.

65
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:09,057
不，尼克 他想見尼克
No, Nick. He wants to see Nick.

66
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:11,768
你仍在折磨布林漢姆？
You still torturing Bringham?

67
00:05:11,936 --> 00:05:14,146
這麼說吧，我不像他那麼看重哈佛學位
Nick: Let's just say I'm less impressed with his Harvard degree than he is.

68
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:15,647
呵，我們不能都去上福德漢姆
Well, we can't all have gone to Fordham.

69
00:05:15,815 --> 00:05:17,065
我上過福德漢姆夜校
I went to Fordham night school.

70
00:05:17,233 --> 00:05:19,443
知道我在福德漢姆夜校學到什麼了嗎？
You know what I learned in Fordham night school?

71
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:20,902
法學院裡學不到什麼法律
Law school's got nothing to do with law.

72
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:23,322
我猜你逃了職場哲學的課
Guess you skipped the course on inter-office politics.

73
00:05:23,489 --> 00:05:26,241
我所需要的就是陪審團喜歡我 這不是你教我的嗎，喬納斯？
All I need is a jury to like me. Isn't that what you told me, Jonas?

74
00:05:26,409 --> 00:05:29,286
謝爾頓案件… 進展到哪了？
The Shelton case- where are we?

75
00:05:29,454 --> 00:05:31,163
昨晚出了點差錯，伯奇法官那邊
It went sideways last night- Judge Burch.

76
00:05:31,331 --> 00:05:32,706
啊…
Ahh.

77
00:05:32,874 --> 00:05:34,666
壞消息，現在怎樣辦？
Bad news. What now?

78
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:37,544
- 作筆交易吧 - 尼克，他們殺了小女孩
- Let's make the deal. - They killed a little girl, Nick.

79
00:05:37,712 --> 00:05:40,589
- 這是一個不完美的體制 - 而我們是不完美公僕
- It's an imperfect system. - And we its imperfect servants.

80
00:05:40,757 --> 00:05:44,343
- 不過，你還是可以贏下這個案子 - 不，不能去冒險
- However you could win this case. - No, can't take that chance.

81
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:47,137
有一些公正總比沒有公正好
Some justice is better than no justice at all.

82
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,306
那你得去告訴那位丈夫
You need to tell the husband.

83
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:51,683
好的 那是我的工作
Okay. That's part of my job.

84
00:05:51,851 --> 00:05:54,811
很好，因為他正在等著你，現在！
Good, because he's waiting for you right now.

85
00:05:54,979 --> 00:05:56,646
什麼？
What?

86
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:08,825
- 你怎麼樣？ - 還好，你怎麼樣？
- How are you doing? - Good. How are you doing?

87
00:06:08,993 --> 00:06:11,578
還好 坐吧，坐吧
Good. Sit. Sit.

88
00:06:11,746 --> 00:06:14,247
呃，一直沒有你的消息
Well, I didn't hear back from you

89
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:17,584
所以我寫了一些東西關於這案子
and made some notes on the case.

90
00:06:17,752 --> 00:06:20,670
我有些好主意
I had some good ideas.

91
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:22,506
好，讓我來看看
Yeah, let me take a look at it.

92
00:06:24,092 --> 00:06:25,884
恩，它們只是…
Well, they're just-

93
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:33,517
我正打算跟你談這個
I was gonna talk to you about those.

94
00:06:34,519 --> 00:06:36,895
你信任我麼？
Do you trust me?

95
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,942
你信任我麼，克萊德？
Do you trust me, Clyde?

96
00:06:43,444 --> 00:06:44,694
是的，當然
Yeah, of course.

97
00:06:47,365 --> 00:06:50,575
多比同意作證檢舉阿米
Darby has agreed to testify against Ames.

98
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:53,328
有了多比的證詞
With Darby's testimony,

99
00:06:53,496 --> 00:06:55,288
阿米就會被判死刑
Ames will go to death row.

100
00:06:59,585 --> 00:07:03,296
嗯，那…多比會怎樣？
Um, what about- what about Darby then?

101
00:07:03,464 --> 00:07:06,967
多比將被定罪謀殺
Darby will plead guilty to murder.

102
00:07:07,135 --> 00:07:09,803
- 幾級？ - 三級
- In what degree? - Third.

103
00:07:09,971 --> 00:07:12,431
他會服刑多久？五年？
He serves, what? Five years...

104
00:07:12,598 --> 00:07:15,183
最多？
at best?

105
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:18,228
很抱歉，我不明白
I don't understand. I'm sorry.

106
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:22,232
我們遇到了麻煩 法官裁定DNA證據不被採用
We had a setback. The judge ruled that the DNA was inadmissible.

107
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:25,360
- 什麼？ - 非法證據排除原則
- What? - Exclusionary rule.

108
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:27,362
辯方律師的伎倆
The opposing counsel maneuvered it.

109
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:29,698
你說過這個部分容易辨認
You said this part of the case was clear-cut.

110
00:07:29,866 --> 00:07:31,366
我們在他的襯衫上發現了血跡
We had the blood on his shirt-

111
00:07:31,534 --> 00:07:33,201
這也涵蓋在同樣的原則下
It's covered under the same rule.

112
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:34,703
那法醫的其它證據呢？
What about the rest of the forensic evidence?

113
00:07:34,871 --> 00:07:38,498
那些都不是決定性的，克萊德
It's not conclusive, Clyde.

114
00:07:40,501 --> 00:07:44,087
好吧，沒關係 我看見…我看見他們的臉了
Okay, that's okay. 'Cause I saw- I saw their faces.

115
00:07:44,255 --> 00:07:47,299
我親眼看到他們行兇 他們殺了我的小女兒，尼克
I saw them do it. I mean, he killed my little girl, Nick.

116
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:50,343
克萊德，你暈過去了 你的證詞無法令人信服
You blacked out, Clyde. Your testimony won't be reliable.

117
00:07:50,511 --> 00:07:53,263
你站上證人席時 辯方律師會把你撕碎的
You get on the stand and the defense will tear you apart.

118
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:55,849
不，不，陪審團會相信我的
No no, the jury's gonna believe me though.

119
00:07:56,017 --> 00:07:59,144
- 因為這就是真相，我們可以… - 我們會輸的
- Because it's the truth! We can- - We can lose.

120
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:02,063
然後我們會一無所獲
And then we'd have nothing.

121
00:08:02,231 --> 00:08:04,608
你會浪費一整年的時間 花費百萬美元
You will waste a whole year, spend millions of dollars,

122
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:06,693
然後他倆雙雙逍遙法外
and then both of them could end up going free.

123
00:08:06,861 --> 00:08:10,405
尼克，他們都有罪 尤其是多比！
Nick, both of them are guilty, especially Darby!

124
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,574
- 你知道這些 - 這與你知道什麼無關，克萊德
- You know that. - It's not what you know, Clyde.

125
00:08:12,742 --> 00:08:15,160
而是你能在法庭上證明什麼
It's what you can prove in court.

126
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,416
請別與這人做這個交易
Please don't make a deal with this man.

127
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:23,627
請別與這人交易，他是禽獸
Please don't make a deal with this man. He's a monster-

128
00:08:23,794 --> 00:08:26,296
對不起，協議已經達成了，對不起
I'm sorry, the deal is done. I'm sorry.

129
00:08:26,464 --> 00:08:28,298
我達成了協議
I made the deal.

130
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:31,426
什麼？你怎麼可以那樣做？
What? How could you do that?

131
00:08:31,594 --> 00:08:35,180
這就是司法體系運作的方式
This is just how the justice system works.

132
00:08:35,348 --> 00:08:39,434
聽著，我知道你現在不認可這點
Listen, I know you don't think it right now,

133
00:08:39,602 --> 00:08:42,354
但這其實是我們的勝利
but this is a victory for us.

134
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,276
你們辦公室已經認可這個協議了嗎？
Woman: Your office has certified this agreement?

135
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:49,694
是的，法官閣下
Yes, Your Honor.

136
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:53,740
雷諾斯先生，今天有無高見與法庭分享？
Mr. Reynolds, any great insights to share with the court today?

137
00:08:53,908 --> 00:08:56,910
我是辯方律師，法官閣下 我沒多少高見
I'm a defense attorney, Your Honor. I don't have many of those.

138
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:03,166
沒有，法官大人，沒有意見了
No, Your Honor. No insights.

139
00:09:03,334 --> 00:09:06,127
很好，那我相信我們可以毫無阻礙地
Good, then I trust that we can move forward with Mr. Ames's trial

140
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:09,798
推進阿米先生的判決了 審批日期將近了
unimpeded by continuances. A triaI date is imminent.

141
00:09:12,927 --> 00:09:14,761
喂？
Yeah?

142
00:09:14,929 --> 00:09:17,305
瑞斯先生，我的法庭不允許講手機
There's no cell phones in my courtroom, Mr. Rice.

143
00:09:17,473 --> 00:09:18,807
- 我們說過了… - 抱歉
- We've been over this- - I'm sorry.

144
00:09:18,975 --> 00:09:20,100
一遍地，又一遍地
- and over this, over this...

145
00:09:20,268 --> 00:09:22,936
是的，我有些急事…
Yeah, I had some exigent business I-

146
00:09:23,104 --> 00:09:25,063
下次我就要沒收了
Next time it's mine.

147
00:09:29,068 --> 00:09:31,736
- 啊，你結婚了嗎？ - 你說什麼？
- Ah, you married? - Excuse me?

148
00:09:31,904 --> 00:09:33,905
你結婚了？
Are you married?

149
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:39,035
請繼續噴 這樣我就能毀了你
Please fuck this up so I can destroy you.

150
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:46,876
我不想害人
I wish ill for no man,

151
00:09:47,044 --> 00:09:50,714
不過阿米罪有應得
but Ames deserves to suffer for what he did.

152
00:09:50,881 --> 00:09:54,050
我是說，你沒法跟天斗的對吧？
I mean, you can't fight fate, right?

153
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:01,266
尼克
Nick.

154
00:10:01,434 --> 00:10:04,019
一旦你做了決定 就要學會接受…繼續往前
Cantrell: Once you make a decision, live with it- move on.

155
00:10:04,186 --> 00:10:06,354
這份工作，最大的資產就是短暫記憶
This job, your best asset's a short memory.

156
00:10:06,522 --> 00:10:09,566
別自責了，其他很多人都這樣干了
Don't beat yourself up. Too many other people out there doing that already.

157
00:10:09,734 --> 00:10:10,984
看，現在那邊就有一些人
Look, there's some of them right now.

158
00:10:11,152 --> 00:10:14,112
是不是到了時間你要給我講些寓言
Isn't this where you tell me some type of old fable

159
00:10:14,280 --> 00:10:17,073
或者啟蒙故事的了
or wives' tale-

160
00:10:17,241 --> 00:10:19,075
好了，好了，我想到一個了
All right, all right, I got one.

161
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:21,161
